{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2015/10/15/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Standalone Code Points</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+2E2E\">U+2E2E</a> REVERSED QUESTION MARK - the “irony\nmark” to express irony/sarcasm. A useful character⸮</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T21:01:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Code Points that Affect Others</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+FE0E\">U+FE0E</a> VARIATION SELECTOR-15 - force\nblack-<em>&#x26;</em>-white emoji. If this code point follows an emoji, an explicit\nmonochrome rendering of the emoji is requested (if the client supports it).</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T21:01:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Record Holders and Extremes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1F402\">U+1F402</a> OX - shortest name.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T21:01:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1DD2\">U+1DD2</a> COMBINING US ABOVE - this is the most\nromantic code point.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T21:01:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1F596\">U+1F596</a> RAISED HAND WITH PART BETWEEN\nMIDDLE AND RING FINGERS - the Vulcan salute. Live long and prosper!\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T21:01:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1F918\">U+1F918</a> SIGN OF THE HORNS - Rock on!\n落</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T21:01:09.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pico-8/awesome-PICO-8","categoryHTML":"<h3>Resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/josefnpat/bfe4aaa5bbb44f572cd0\">Going from Lua 5.2 to PICO-8's Lua</a> - This document is here to help folks with a proficiency in Lua understand the limitations and discrepencies between Lua and PICO-8's Lua.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T20:37:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"drewrwilson/toolsforactivism","categoryHTML":"<h2>Projects to keep an eye on (ie projects in development)</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://drewrwilson.com/stencilvalidator/\">Stencil Validator</a> (<a href=\"https://github.com/drewrwilson/stencilvalidator\">code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/drewrwilson/stencilvalidator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":12,\"repo\":\"drewrwilson/stencilvalidator\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) - a design tool for determining if your artwork is a valid stencil</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T19:36:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"lucasviola/awesome-tech-videos","categoryHTML":"<h3>Motivation</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hN63FOa_Gp4\">Impossible Programming</a> By Tom Stuart</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T18:12:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"wbkd/awesome-d3","categoryHTML":"<h2>Miscellaneous</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sebastian-meier/d3.sketchy\">d3.sketchy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sebastian-meier/d3.sketchy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">241</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":241,\"repo\":\"sebastian-meier/d3.sketchy\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Creates sketchy backgrounds, shapes and lines</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T18:02:25.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Standalone Code Points</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+D800\">U+D800</a> to\n<a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+DFFF\">U+DFFF</a> - surrogate code points. They are\nonly reserved to ease <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-16\">UTF-16\nencoding</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Standalone Code Points</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+FFFD\">U+FFFD</a> REPLACEMENT CHARACTER - when a\ncharacter cannot be displayed (e.g., decoding an erroneous UTF-8 sequency),\nthis code point steps into the breach.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Standalone Code Points</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1D455\">U+1D455</a> is missing. It would be an italic\nsmall “h”. It was not encoded, because it would be identical to the Planck\nconstant ℎ (<a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+210E\">U+210E</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Code Points that Affect Others</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+202D\">U+202D</a> and\n<a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+202E\">U+202E</a> - change the text direction.\nRelevant XKCD:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://xkcd.com/1137/\"><img src=\"http://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/rtl.png\" alt=\"\"></a></p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Code Points that Affect Others</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p>Diacritics and combining marks: There is a <a href=\"https://codepoints.net/search?gc=Mn\">host of\ncharacters</a>, that add\nto the characters before. Those are called Combining Marks. Unicode\nprovides a <a href=\"http://unicode.org/faq/char_combmark.html\">handy FAQ</a> on the\ndetails, but in a nutshell: If you add one after a character, it is placed\non top of that previous one. So, <code>a + ̊ = å</code>. This <em>may</em> lead to all kinds\nof funny problems, because for some combinations there are pre-composed\ncharacters. Our little <code>å</code> here can also be encoded as U+00E5. You might\nnote, that while this has a length of one character, the combination of <code>a</code>\nand combining ring has a length of two characters.</p>\n<p>Of course, one can also do fun things with those characters like\n<a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/a/1732454/113195\">this answer</a> on StackOverflow.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Record Holders and Extremes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+FDFA\">U+FDFA</a> ARABIC LIGATURE SALLALLAHOU ALAYHE\nWASALLAM - longest decomposition form: 18 characters.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1680\">U+1680</a> OGHAM SPACE MARK - a space that looks\nlike a dash. Great to bring programmers close to madness: <code>1 +  2 === 3</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+037E\">U+037E</a> GREEK QUESTION MARK - a look-alike to\nthe semicolon. Also a fun way to annoy developers.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+F8FF\">U+F8FF</a> PRIVATE USE CODEPOINT - this private\nuse code point is rendered as Apple logo on many Apple devices.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>For Funsies</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+1F574\">U+1F574</a> MAN IN BUSINESS SUIT LEVITATING -\nA rather curious character, that only made it into Unicode for its\nappearance in the Webdings font (for reasons of backwards compatibility).</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-15T10:38:44.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1444867200000,"to":1444953599999,"previousId":"2015-10-16","nextId":"2015-10-14","nextName":"Oct 14th, 2015","previousName":"Oct 16th, 2015"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}